                            <comment id="13291920" author="jlowe" created="Fri, 8 Jun 2012 19:17:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to update the Netty dependency to 3.2.4.Final which has the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/NETTY-374&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;NETTY-374&lt;/a&gt;.  Manually tested with the issue described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAPREDUCE-4298&quot; title=&quot;NodeManager crashed after running out of file descriptors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAPREDUCE-4298&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAPREDUCE-4298&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to verify file descriptors are no longer leaked when I/O errors occur on the channel.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
